            array('id' => '25','source_url' => env('APP_URL').'/message/25/notice-of-general-meeting-monday-december-16th-2024-700-pm','subject' => 'NOTICE OF GENERAL MEETING Monday December 16th 2024 7:00 PM','slug' => 'notice-of-general-meeting-monday-december-16th-2024-700-pm','content' => '<p><a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://us06web.zoom.us/meeting/register/tZMlfu2rpjgqHtdZEzYGkm5DdKwj8pohnapq"><strong>Sign Up Here!</strong></a></p><p>The Next General Meeting of IATSE Local 118 will be held digitally Via a Zoom Webinar on Monday, December 16th @ 7:00 PM</p><p><br>Dear Brothers, Sisters, and Kin:<br><br>To ensure security, members must register in advance. You will be sent a confirmation email with the details on how to join the meeting no less than 24 hours prior to the Call to Order.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><h3>General Meeting Agenda</h3><p>On the agenda for this meeting:</p><ul><li>&nbsp;Approval of minutes from the previous General Meeting. &nbsp;</li><li>Reports, as outlined in the Constitution and By-Laws</li><li>New Business</li></ul><p>Any members or committees with business for the agenda must submit them to office@iatse118.com 48 hours in advance of the General Meeting.</p><h3>Guidelines for attending a Zoom meeting:</h3><p>Zoom can be run in your browser, but it will be easier if you download the app here: https://zoom.us/download.<br>In accordance with a directive from the International, attendees of all remote local 118 meetings will be required to keep their cameras on at all times except during break periods. Should an attendee be out of frame or have their camera turned off for a sustained time they will be removed from the meeting until they can reappear on camera.<br>Members will be able to “raise their hand” to ask questions and will be recognized by the Chair prior to having their microphone unmuted.<br>Members will also be able to type in their questions in the chat box.<br>The chat will be monitored by a member of the Executive. Points of Order and Points of Privilege can be submitted via the chat function and will be immediately addressed by the Chair.<br>Voting on motions will take place using the “poll” function.<br>&nbsp;Remember: General Meetings are confidential union business. Make sure that you are in a location where you cannot be overheard by non-members.<br>If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact the Executive Board ​at office@iatse118.com<br>&nbsp;</p>','user_id' => '1','count' => '0','state' => 'sent','created_at' => '2024-12-12 03:13:53','updated_at' => '2024-12-12 03:18:22'),
            array('id' => '26','source_url' => env('APP_URL').'/message/26/ballet-bc-contract-discussion-meeting','subject' => 'Ballet BC Contract Discussion Meeting','slug' => 'ballet-bc-contract-discussion-meeting','content' => '<div class="elementToProof" style="-webkit-text-size-adjust:auto;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;color:#000000;font-family:Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:auto;text-align:start;text-decoration:none;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:auto;word-spacing:0px;">Dear 118 Members,</div><div class="elementToProof" style="-webkit-text-size-adjust:auto;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;color:#000000;font-family:Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:auto;text-align:start;text-decoration:none;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:auto;word-spacing:0px;">&nbsp;</div><div class="elementToProof" style="-webkit-text-size-adjust:auto;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;color:#000000;font-family:Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:auto;text-align:start;text-decoration:none;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:auto;word-spacing:0px;">The Union has reached a tentative deal with Ballet BC for renewal of the 118-Ballet BC Collective Agreement</div><div class="elementToProof" style="-webkit-text-size-adjust:auto;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;color:#000000;font-family:Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:auto;text-align:start;text-decoration:none;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:auto;word-spacing:0px;">&nbsp;</div><div class="elementToProof" style="-webkit-text-size-adjust:auto;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;color:#000000;font-family:Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:auto;text-align:start;text-decoration:none;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:auto;word-spacing:0px;">The Ballet BC Bargaining Committee would like to invite you to a discussion regarding the memorandum of settlement on <strong>December 12th at 5:00pm via Zoom. </strong>The meeting is open to all 118 members, but only members who have worked under the Ballet contract in its previous term will be eligible to vote on the ratification.<br><br>The ratification ballot will open on the morning of Friday December 13th and close at 5 PM on Monday December 16th.</div><div class="elementToProof" style="-webkit-text-size-adjust:auto;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;color:#000000;font-family:Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:auto;text-align:start;text-decoration:none;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:auto;word-spacing:0px;">&nbsp;</div><div class="elementToProof" style="-webkit-text-size-adjust:auto;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;color:#000000;font-family:Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:auto;text-align:start;text-decoration:none;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:auto;word-spacing:0px;">Ballet BC Contract Ratification Zoom Link:<br><a style="-ms-text-size-adjust:100%;-webkit-text-size-adj